{{2016年夏季奥林匹克运动会}}
2016年8月在[[巴西|巴西]][[里约热内卢|里约热内卢]]举办的[[2016年夏季奥林匹克运动会|2016年夏季奥林匹克运动会]]出现一系列的'''相关问题'''，引起了媒体和公众的关注。

== 賽事關注度疲弱 ==
雖然是全球4年一度的體育盛事，但基於娛樂選擇增多，加上巴西籌辦奧運的報導等條件，令奧運關注度比以往低<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.new7.com.tw/talk/talkView.aspx?i=TXT20160720144047M1C|title=新新聞-【競技場上】奧運  國際政治角力盛會|accessdate=2016-10-03|work=www.new7.com.tw|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161003190347/http://www.new7.com.tw/talk/talkView.aspx?i=TXT20160720144047M1C|archive-date=2016-10-03|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

==本身存在的問題==
=== 茲卡病毒 ===
[[File:Exército_Brasileiro_no_combate_ao_mosquito_Aedes_(24626830366).jpg|thumb]]

奥运会前爆发的[[寨卡病毒疫情_(2015-2016年)|茲卡病毒疫情]]引发运动员和游客的担忧。组织者计划每天对奥运场馆进行检查，防止积水滋生蚊虫<ref>{{cite news|title=Zika virus: Olympic venues to be inspected daily before and during Games|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/olympics/35444254|accessdate=2016-01-30|publisher=BBC Sport|date=2016-01-29|archive-date=2016-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129203943/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/olympics/35444254|dead-url=no}}</ref>。茲卡病毒的传播也被认为与该地区低效的污水处理有关，主办方已采取措施改善污水状况<ref name="atlantic 20160331"/>。

许多人呼吁推迟举办奥运会，并警告称50万名预期国际游客的出现可能会导致病毒在国外迅速传播<ref name="nyt-zikarisks">{{cite web|title=Researchers Weigh Risks of Zika Spreading at Rio Olympics|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/29/world/americas/brazil-zika-rio-olympics.html?_r=0|website=The New York Times|accessdate=2016-05-31|archive-date=2016-02-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160201071251/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/29/world/americas/brazil-zika-rio-olympics.html?_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2016年第一季度的[[登革热|登革热]]病例比2015年全年要多<ref name="quartz-goahead"/><ref name="wp-150experts"/>。[[渥太华大学|渥太华大学]]的阿米尔·阿塔兰教授（{{lang|en|Dr. Amir Attaran}}）在《哈佛公共卫生评论》（{{lang|en|Harvard Public Health Review}}）文章中指出，里约有着巴西各州中最集中的茲卡传染病。他认为，奥运会可能会导致茲卡爆发的“全球性灾难”，并表示允许比赛继续进行是“对社会的极不负责任”，“在道德上有问题”。另一方面，据称计算机模型和模拟的实证和比赛在蚊子活动减少的[[南半球|南半球]]冬季举行的事实，证明比赛期间茲卡的威胁不会很高。然而，茲卡在巴西爆发初期也在冬季的几个月发生，但赤道附近的东北部国家在地理上全年无冬。[[美国疾病控制与预防中心|美国疾病控制与预防中心]]主任{{le|汤姆·弗利登|Tom Frieden}}表示，“公众健康原因不能取消或推迟奥运会<ref name="quartz-goahead">{{cite web|title="The Games will go ahead": Tourists have a near-zero chance of getting Zika at the Rio Olympics|url=http://qz.com/682702/the-games-will-go-ahead-tourists-have-a-near-zero-chance-of-getting-zika-at-the-rio-olympics/|website=Quartz|accessdate=2015-06-31|archive-date=2016-05-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160526124331/http://qz.com/682702/the-games-will-go-ahead-tourists-have-a-near-zero-chance-of-getting-zika-at-the-rio-olympics/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="wp-150experts">{{cite web|title=150 experts say Olympics must be moved or postponed because of Zika|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/to-your-health/wp/2016/05/27/125-experts-say-olympics-must-be-moved-or-postponed-because-of-zika/|website=Washington Post|accessdate=2016-05-31|archive-date=2016-06-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160602191555/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/to-your-health/wp/2016/05/27/125-experts-say-olympics-must-be-moved-or-postponed-because-of-zika/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="hplr-offthepodium">{{cite journal|last1=Attaran|first1=Amir|title=Off the Podium: Why Public Health Concerns for Global Spread of Zika Virus Means That Rio de Janeiro's 2016 Olympic Games Must Not Proceed|journal=Harvard Public Health Review|url=http://harvardpublichealthreview.org/off-the-podium-why-rios-2016-olympic-games-must-not-proceed/|access-date=2016-08-08|archive-date=2016-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160728195839/http://harvardpublichealthreview.org/off-the-podium-why-rios-2016-olympic-games-must-not-proceed/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |accessdate=2016-03-08 |first1=Didier |last1=Musso |url=http://wwwnc.cdc.gov/eid/article/21/10/15-1125_article |title=Zika Virus Transmission from French Polynesia to Brazil |publisher=Centers for Disease Control and Prevention |date=October 2015 |journal=Emerging Infectious Diseases |volume=21 |issue=10 |page=1887 |doi=10.3201/eid2110.151125 |archive-date=2016-03-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320003447/http://wwwnc.cdc.gov/eid/article/21/10/15-1125_article |dead-url=no }}</ref>。”

2016年5月，150名医生和科学家联名公开上书[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]，呼吁他们按照信起草者[[亚瑟·卡普兰|亚瑟·卡普兰]]的说法，“公开透明讨论如期在巴西举办奥运会的风险”。世卫驳回了要求，指出“取消或改变2016年奥运会举办地不会明显改变茲卡病毒的国际传播”，也没有“公众健康原因”能推迟比赛<ref name="quartz-goahead"/><ref name="wp-150experts"/><ref name="bbc-whono">{{cite web|title=Zika crisis: WHO rejects 'move Rio Olympics' call|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-36401150|website=BBC News|accessdate=2016-05-31|archive-date=2016-05-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160530025637/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-36401150|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

许多运动员因担心寨卡病毒而退赛，其中包括[[米洛斯·拉奥尼奇|米洛斯·拉奥尼奇]]<ref name="np-raonicout">{{cite web|title=Milos Raonic withdraws from Rio Olympics citing ‘variety of health concerns’|url=http://news.nationalpost.com/sports/tennis/milos-raonic-withdraws-from-rio-olympics-citing-variety-of-health-concerns|website=National Post (Canada)|accessdate=2016-07-15|archive-date=2016-07-24|archive-url=https://archive.is/20160724135136/http://news.nationalpost.com/sports/tennis/milos-raonic-withdraws-from-rio-olympics-citing-variety-of-health-concerns|dead-url=no}}</ref>、[[托马斯·伯蒂奇|托马斯·伯蒂奇]]<ref name="trio">{{cite web|last1=Murray|first1=Ewan|title=Jordan Spieth’s Rio Olympics refusal sparks claim of Zika ‘overreaction’|url=http://www.insidethegames.biz/index.php/articles/1039658/top-tennis-trio-withdraw-from-rio-2016-tennis-tournament-due-to-zika|website=Inside the Games|accessdate=2016-07-12|archive-date=2016-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160808014511/http://www.insidethegames.biz/index.php/articles/1039658/top-tennis-trio-withdraw-from-rio-2016-tennis-tournament-due-to-zika|dead-url=no}}</ref>、[[西莫娜·哈勒普|西莫娜·哈勒普]]<ref name="trio" />、[[卡罗琳娜·普利斯科娃|卡罗琳娜·普利斯科娃]]<ref name="espn-johnsonout">{{cite web|title=RIO OLYMPICS - Karolina Pliskova Withdraws due to Zika|url=http://www.tennisworldusa.org/RIO-OLYMPICS---Karolina-Pliskova-Wi-articolo34556.html|website=Tennis World|accessdate=2016-07-27|archive-date=2019-09-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190912093143/https://www.tennisworldusa.org/tennis/news/Tennis_Stories/34556/rio-olympics-karolina-pliskova-withdraws-due-to-zika/|dead-url=no}}</ref>、{{le|杰森·戴|Jason Day}}<ref name="atlantic-sayingno">{{cite web|title=The Athletes Saying No to the Olympics Over Zika|url=http://www.theatlantic.com/news/archive/2016/06/olympic-zika-jason-day/489113/|website=The Atlantic|accessdate=2016-07-12|archive-date=2016-07-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701165921/http://www.theatlantic.com/news/archive/2016/06/olympic-zika-jason-day/489113/|dead-url=no}}</ref>、{{le|特贾·范·加德兰|Tejay van Garderen}}、[[布兰登·格雷斯|布兰登·格雷斯]]、[[达斯汀·约翰逊|达斯汀·约翰逊]]<ref name="#1">{{cite web|title=Dustin Johnson cites Zika virus as reason for withdrawing from Games|url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/story/_/id/16909678/dustin-johnson-withdraws-olympics-citing-zika-virus-concerns|website=ESPN.com|accessdate=2016-07-12|archive-date=2016-07-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160712155605/http://espn.go.com/olympics/story/_/id/16909678/dustin-johnson-withdraws-olympics-citing-zika-virus-concerns|dead-url=no}}</ref>、[[肖恩·劳瑞|肖恩·劳瑞]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Rio Olympics 2016: Jason Day and Shane Lowry pull out over Zika fears|url=http://www.bbc.com/sport/golf/36653416|website=BBC|accessdate=2016-06-28|archive-date=2016-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160702071535/http://www.bbc.com/sport/golf/36653416|dead-url=no}}</ref>、[[罗伊·麦克罗伊|罗伊·麦克罗伊]]、[[马克·莱许曼|马克·莱许曼]]、[[查尔·舒瓦特泽尔|查尔·舒瓦特泽尔]]、{{le|安杰洛·奎伊|Angelo Que}}<ref name="#1"/>和[[乔丹·斯皮思|乔丹·斯皮思]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Golfer Angelo Que cites Zika in pulling out of Rio|url=http://www.philstar.com/sports/2016/07/13/1602462/golfer-angelo-que-cites-zika-pulling-out-rio|accessdate=2016-07-13|archive-date=2016-09-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160917193303/http://www.philstar.com/sports/2016/07/13/1602462/golfer-angelo-que-cites-zika-pulling-out-rio|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="guardian-overreacting">{{cite web|last1=Murray|first1=Ewan|title=Jordan Spieth’s Rio Olympics refusal sparks claim of Zika ‘overreaction’|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/jul/11/jordan-spieth-rio-olympics-claim-zika-overreaction|website=The Guardian|accessdate=2016-07-12|archive-date=2016-07-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160711213203/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/jul/11/jordan-spieth-rio-olympics-claim-zika-overreaction|dead-url=no}}</ref>。有鉴于大多数退赛的运动员都是高尔夫球手，[[国际高尔夫总会|国际高尔夫总会]]主席彼得·道森（{{lang|en|Peter Dawson}}）认为对寨卡病毒的反应过度，表示：“我认为现在不适宜讨论个别例子，尤其是他们通常以健康为由作决定。但从大局上讲，毫无疑问退赛人数影响到高尔夫球赛的正常进行。我们必须接受这一点。但是我要了解这些人作出决定的原因<ref name="guardian-overreacting"/>。”不過這個事件已經影響到[[2020年夏季奧林匹克運動會|下一屆]]的奧運的高爾夫球考慮只舉辦女子項目。<ref>{{cite news|title=數萬軍力投入奧運 未來可能停辦男高球賽|url=http://news.xn--1qws34d.com/NewsContent.aspx?ntype=class&sno=2016715A04M1#|accessdate=|agency=|date=|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823023625/http://news.xn--1qws34d.com/NewsContent.aspx?ntype=class&sno=2016715A04M1|archivedate=2016-08-23}}</ref>

=== 卫生 ===
[[File:Marina_da_Glória_1.jpg|thumb]]比赛地点[[格洛里亚码头|格洛里亚码头]]]]
举办帆船和帆板比赛的[[瓜纳巴拉湾|瓜纳巴拉湾]]污染严重，首要原因是未经回收的垃圾透过受污染的河流和沿海棚户区流入湾区。瓜纳巴拉湾是长期的问题，尽管官员在1992年[[地球高峰会|地球高峰会]]上承诺将着手解决污染，但此前的尝试都不奏效。里约在申办奥运会时曾再次承诺努力清理湾区<ref name="nyt-pollution">{{cite web|title=Note to Olympic Sailors: Don’t Fall in Rio's Water|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/19/world/americas/memo-to-olympic-sailors-in-rio-dont-touch-the-water.html?_r=0|website=The New York Times|accessdate=2016-05-06|archive-date=2016-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160801195405/http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/19/world/americas/memo-to-olympic-sailors-in-rio-dont-touch-the-water.html?_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-25686805 |title=Rio's Olympic waters blighted by heavy pollution |last1=Carneiro |first1=Julia |last2= |first2= |date=2014-01-10 |website=BBC News |accessdate=2014-01-12 |archive-date=2014-01-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140111141738/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-25686805 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。然而，其中一些提议举措面临着预算问题<ref name="guardian-fundingclean">{{cite web|last1=Baich|first1=Oliver|title=Funding problems hit plan to clean Rio's polluted waterways ahead of Olympics|url=http://www.theguardian.com/sustainable-business/2016/feb/01/funding-problems-hit-plan-clean-rios-polluted-waterways-olympics|website=The Guardian|accessdate=2016-05-06|archive-date=2016-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160507143010/http://www.theguardian.com/sustainable-business/2016/feb/01/funding-problems-hit-plan-clean-rios-polluted-waterways-olympics|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

经过此前的努力，里约有17%的污水被处理<ref name="guardian-germannfect"/>，未处理过的污水也被泄露到湾区。2011年，新的财团接手里约西部用于奥运会传统项目的“AP5”区的污水处理。财团致力于打造出升级污水系统，到2016年底将流入湾区的污水量减少到1700万加仑。然而，新系统的采用进展缓慢，安装费用的不一致引发居民担忧<ref name="wp-sewagerio">{{cite web|title=Rio planned Olympic-scale sewerage project. But citizens say no thanks.|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/the_americas/rio-planned-olympic-scale-sewerage-project-but-citizens-say-no-thanks/2016/01/06/bcc13362-a91f-11e5-b596-113f59ee069a_story.html|website=Washington Post|accessdate=2016-05-06|archive-date=2016-05-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160523035248/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/the_americas/rio-planned-olympic-scale-sewerage-project-but-citizens-say-no-thanks/2016/01/06/bcc13362-a91f-11e5-b596-113f59ee069a_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。尽管市长{{le|爱德华多·帕埃斯|Eduardo Paes}}表示城市无法达到处理80%污水的目标<ref name="wp-superbug"/>，但到2016年3月至少有60%的污水被处理，到奥运会开幕时的预期目标是处理65%的污水<ref>{{cite web | title=USOC, athletes navigate questions swirling around Rio’s contaminated water | website=Washington Post | date=2016-03-09 | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/olympics/us-athletes-focused-on-medals-not-water-quality-ahead-of-rio-olympics/2016/03/09/def96766-e63b-11e5-b0fd-073d5930a7b7_story.html | accessdate=2016-06-30 | archive-date=2016-06-19 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160619130452/https://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/olympics/us-athletes-focused-on-medals-not-water-quality-ahead-of-rio-olympics/2016/03/09/def96766-e63b-11e5-b0fd-073d5930a7b7_story.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

污水引发对比赛和运动员健康影响，尤其是受污染的水道无法让运动员比赛的担忧<ref name="atlantic 20160331">{{cite web | last=Khazan | first=Olga | title=What Happens When There's Poop in the Water | website=The Atlantic | date=2016-03-31 | url=http://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2016/03/what-happens-when-theres-sewage-in-the-water/476013/ | accessdate=2016-06-30 | archive-date=2016-07-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160702140437/http://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2016/03/what-happens-when-theres-sewage-in-the-water/476013/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。2014年，在湾区训练的水手告诉《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》，他们必须为躲避在水面上漂浮的从轮胎到狗的尸体等各种各样的垃圾而斗争<ref name="nyt-pollution"/>。同年12月，[[奥斯瓦尔多·克鲁斯基金会|奥斯瓦尔多·克鲁斯基金会]]从{{le|卡里奥卡河|Carioca River}}水样中检出耐药的“超级细菌”KPK酶。他们警告称“携带者可以将这些抗药细菌带回自己的环境，传染给其他人，引发传播周期”<ref name="wp-superbug">{{cite web|title=‘Super bacteria’ found in Rio waters where sailors and windsurfers are supposed to compete in the Olympics|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2014/12/17/super-bacteria-found-in-rio-waters-where-sailors-and-windsurfers-are-supposed-to-compete-in-the-olympics/|website=Washington Post|accessdate=2016-05-06|archive-date=2016-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160609202221/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2014/12/17/super-bacteria-found-in-rio-waters-where-sailors-and-windsurfers-are-supposed-to-compete-in-the-olympics/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="rt-superbug">{{cite web|title=Drug-resistant ‘superbug’ found in Rio de Janeiro Olympic waters|url=https://www.rt.com/news/214807-brazil-olympic-venue-superbug/|website=RT|accessdate=2016-05-06|archive-date=2016-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603024007/https://www.rt.com/news/214807-brazil-olympic-venue-superbug/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2015年，据发现由于开放排水和严重的污染，里约水道“致病病毒”发病率被检测出是“南加州海滩危险程度的170万倍”<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/d92f6af5121f49d982601a657d745e95/ap-investigation-rios-olympic-water-rife-sewage-virus|title=Olympic teams to swim, boat in Rio's filth|author1=Brad Brooks|author2=Jenny Barchfield|date=2015-07-30|publisher=Associated Press|accessdate=2016-08-08|archive-date=2016-03-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160324080502/http://bigstory.ap.org/article/d92f6af5121f49d982601a657d745e95/ap-investigation-rios-olympic-water-rife-sewage-virus|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2015年8月的测试赛结束后，德国选手[[埃里克·海尔|埃里克·海尔]]被发现感染据信与污水有关的多种耐药菌<ref name="guardian-germannfect">{{cite news |url=http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2015/aug/28/german-sailor-erik-heil-infections-polluted-water-rio-2016-olympics |title=German sailor blames infections on water at Rio 2016 Olympic test event |work=The Guardian |date=2015-08-28 |accessdate=2016-01-03 |archive-date=2016-01-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160108195621/http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2015/aug/28/german-sailor-erik-heil-infections-polluted-water-rio-2016-olympics |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 政局动荡和经济困境 ===
[[File:Atos_pró_e_contra_o_impeachment_na_Esplanada.jpg|thumb]]派（右）于2016年4月17日下议院投票弹劾总统时聚集在国会前]]
2014年，[[巴西联邦警察|巴西联邦警察]]开展{{le|洗车行动|Operation Car Wash}}，发现国营石油公司[[巴西石油|巴西石油]]前所未有的[[洗钱|洗钱]]和腐败行为，其中高管涉嫌收受贿赂，以换取建筑公司的高价发包。2015年初，巴西爆发一连串针对[[巴西总统|总统]][[迪尔玛·罗塞夫|迪尔玛·罗塞夫]]政府涉嫌腐败的抗议，许多政界人士被爆出牵涉巴西石油公司事件。到2016年年初，丑闻升级为全面爆发的政治危机，不仅影响到总统罗塞夫，还牵涉到前总统[[路易斯·伊纳西奥·卢拉·达席尔瓦|路易斯·伊纳西奥·卢拉·达席尔瓦]]，导致全国各地爆发数百万人参与的示威游行，反对和亲罗塞夫派份子兼有。亲罗塞夫派表示反政府示威者以腐败的名义铲除国家最高领导人，用在洗车行动期间被调查、想要中断调查的政治取代她。他们的怀疑因原本计划在罗塞夫被解任后出任计划部部长的参议员罗梅罗·胡卡（{{lang|pt|Romero Jucá}}）与前石油公司高管塞尔吉奥·马扎罗（{{lang|pt|Sergio Machado}}）一致同意铲除罗塞夫是结束调查的唯一途径的画面被录下来而经证实。《{{le|民族报|The Nation}}》的戴夫·齐林（{{lang|pt|Dave Zirin}}）指出里约奥运会有助于巩固[[政变|政变]]。

与此同时，巴西面临着自20世纪90年代以来最严重的经济衰退，这引发了该国在这样不稳定的政治和经济衰退背景下充分做好奥运会准备的问题。[[经济合作与发展组织|经济合作与发展组织]]一位发言人表示巴西的经济衰退将忍受到2018年，只能通过举行新选举来解决。国际奥委会反而表示经济与政治发展关系“非常密切”。4月14日，奥运安保协调小组确信经济和政治危机不会影响赛事的安全和实现<ref>{{cite news|title=G1 - Crise no RJ e no país não afetará Rio-2016, dizem autoridades|url=http://g1.globo.com/rio-de-janeiro/olimpiadas/rio2016/noticia/2016/04/crise-no-rj-e-no-pais-nao-afetara-rio-2016-dizem-autoridades.html|accessdate=2016-04-14|agency=Globo.com|date=2016-04-24|language=pt|archive-date=2016-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160708021405/http://g1.globo.com/rio-de-janeiro/olimpiadas/rio2016/noticia/2016/04/crise-no-rj-e-no-pais-nao-afetara-rio-2016-dizem-autoridades.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在[[奥林匹亚|奥林匹亚]]的[[奥林匹克圣火|奥林匹克圣火]]采集仪式的演讲中，国际奥委会主席[[托马斯·巴赫|托马斯·巴赫]]评价巴西的政治环境：“这将会是巴西人的奥运会，尽管该国面临着诸多困难，但赛事会将希望的迅速带给其领土和全世界的每一个角落。赛事将会在世界被诸多危机震撼的时候举办。我要赞扬在几个星期内将以热情迎接全世界，让每个人惊讶于运动的喜悦和激情的巴西民众<ref>{{cite news|title=Pesquisa Ibope mostra que 62% preferem novas eleições presidenciais|url=http://veja.abril.com.br/noticia/esporte/rio-2016-tocha-olimpica-e-acesa-em-cerimonia-na-grecia|accessdate=2016-04-24|agency=Veja.com.br|date=2016-04-21|language=pt|archive-date=2016-07-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701111632/http://veja.abril.com.br/noticia/esporte/rio-2016-tocha-olimpica-e-acesa-em-cerimonia-na-grecia|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”

5月12日，经过[[联邦参议院_(巴西)|联邦参议员]]投票[[弹劾|弹劾]]，总统罗塞夫被剥夺权利和职务达半年，因此副总统[[米歇尔·特梅尔|米歇尔·特梅尔]]将在赛事期间代任总统<ref>{{cite news|title=Pesquisa Ibope mostra que 62% preferem novas eleições presidenciais|url=http://g1.globo.com/politica/processo-de-impeachment-de-dilma/noticia/2016/05/processo-de-impeachment-e-aberto-e-dilma-e-afastada-por-ate-180-dias.html|accessdate=2016-05-12|agency=Globo.com|date=2016-05-30|language=pt|archive-date=2016-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160728014404/http://g1.globo.com/politica/processo-de-impeachment-de-dilma/noticia/2016/05/processo-de-impeachment-e-aberto-e-dilma-e-afastada-por-ate-180-dias.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。罗塞夫将不会受邀出席赛事期间的任何活动。相反，以国家元首名义发出的主要邀请将被送给代任总统的副总统特梅尔，尽管特梅尔的合法性受到质疑<ref>{{cite news|title=Pesquisa Ibope mostra que 62% preferem novas eleições presidenciais|url=http://noticias.terra.com.br/brasil/politica/impeachment/rio-2016-convidara-temer-e-nao-dilma-para-abertura-dos-jogos-olimpicos,90f4dbc7d60efe0654d93b6ecbe719fbypfk9fkd.html|accessdate=2016-04-29|agency=Terra.com.br|date=2016-04-30|language=pt|archive-date=2016-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160810180824/https://noticias.terra.com.br/brasil/politica/impeachment/rio-2016-convidara-temer-e-nao-dilma-para-abertura-dos-jogos-olimpicos,90f4dbc7d60efe0654d93b6ecbe719fbypfk9fkd.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在此前的弹劾投票中，绝大多数巴西人支持举行新的大选，以此解决政治危机，只有8%的人支持特梅尔掌权<ref>{{cite news|title=Pesquisa Ibope mostra que 62% preferem novas eleições presidenciais|url=http://g1.globo.com/politica/processo-de-impeachment-de-dilma/noticia/2016/04/pesquisa-ibope-mostra-que-62-preferem-novas-eleicoes-presidenciais.html|accessdate=2016-06-05|agency=G1|date=2016-04-25|language=pt|archive-date=2016-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160608121743/http://g1.globo.com/politica/processo-de-impeachment-de-dilma/noticia/2016/04/pesquisa-ibope-mostra-que-62-preferem-novas-eleicoes-presidenciais.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。里约记者格伦·格林沃尔德称弹劾过程是“巴西精英意图犯下的反民主骗局<ref name="cred">{{cite news|last=Greenwald|first=Glenn|title=Credibility of Brazil's Interim President Collapses as He Receives 8-Year Ban on Running for Office|url=https://theintercept.com/2016/06/03/credibility-of-brazils-interim-president-collapses-receives-8-year-ban-on-running/|accessdate=2016-06-05|agency=The Intercept|date=2016-06-03|archive-date=2016-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160605000036/https://theintercept.com/2016/06/03/credibility-of-brazils-interim-president-collapses-receives-8-year-ban-on-running/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”由于预感到结果，反特梅尔示威正愈演愈烈<ref name="cred"/>。当以色列法语频道[[i24news|i24news]]问道政治危机可能会给奥运会带来的影响时，里约联邦议员{{le|让·威利斯|Jean Wyllys}}表示赛事在动荡政局中举行。他表示：“社会运动和民间社会组织将参与公民抗命、街头抗议，政府可能会采用镇压武力来对抗平民。”威利斯不相信暴力，虽然他声称“社会运动会尊重奥运游客，同时举办和平示威活动对抗非法政府”<ref>{{cite AV media | people =  | date = 2016-04-24 | title = Interview exclusive avec Jean Wyllys, député brésilien sur la crise politique: "un coup d'état" | trans-title = Exclusive interview with Jean Wyllys, Brazilian deputy regarding the political crisis: "a coup d'état" | medium = YouTube视频 | language = fr | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s9dE5OZXZZY | access-date =  | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190214160838/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s9dE5OZXZZY | archive-date = 2019-02-14 | format =  | time =  | location = Israel | publisher = i24news | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

