8月14日，美国游泳运动员[[瑞安·洛赫特|瑞安·洛赫特]]声称和三位队友[[古纳·本茨|古纳·本茨]]、[[杰克·康格|杰克·康格]]、[[吉米·费根|吉米·费根]]一同遭遇假警察持枪抢劫。之后巴西警方展开调查，未能找到证据，怀疑“抢劫”这一说法的真实性。17日，里约当地法院裁定扣留四人的护照，要求其留在巴西境内配合调查，但当时美国游泳队已经离开。巴西警方一度登上飞机，带走了古纳·本茨和杰克·康格两人，要求其配合调查。此时瑞安·洛赫特已于前一日回到美国。<ref>{{cite web|title=American Swimmers Pulled Off Plane in Rio|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/08/18/world/americas/ryan-lochte-rio-olympics.html|publisher=New York Times|accessdate=2016-08-19|archive-date=2016-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160819040843/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/08/18/world/americas/ryan-lochte-rio-olympics.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=US swimmers Gunnar Bentz and Jack Conger stopped at Rio airport|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-37114383|publisher=BBC|accessdate=2016-08-19|archive-date=2016-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818141910/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-37114383|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Lochte, Brazil police differ on robbery; 2 US swimmers heading home|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/08/18/sport/us-swimmers-olympics-robbery-questions/|publisher=CNN|accessdate=2016-08-19|archive-date=2019-09-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190912093143/https://edition.cnn.com/2016/08/19/sport/us-swimmers-olympics-robbery-questions|dead-url=no}}</ref>巴西警方在调查后认为，洛赫特等人的故事纯属虚构。警方查看了四人声称被抢劫当晚的监控录像，指出四人在进入奥运村安检时，钱包并未被抢走，四人神情也十分轻松。警方还在一座加油站的监控中发现，四人损坏了加油站的洗手间，之后与持枪的保安发生了冲突。警方认为四人伪造了“抢劫”的情节，以掩盖破坏公物的事实。<ref name="#2">{{cite web|title=Ryan Lochte and other disgraced US swimmers could be charged for 'vandalism and fabricating robbery'|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/olympics/news/ryan-lochte-and-other-disgraced-us-swimmers-could-be-charged-for-vandalising-toilet-and-fabricating-a7198291.html|publisher=The Independent|accessdate=2016-08-19|archive-date=2016-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160819015024/http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/olympics/news/ryan-lochte-and-other-disgraced-us-swimmers-could-be-charged-for-vandalising-toilet-and-fabricating-a7198291.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ryan Lochte ‘robbed’: US Olympic swimmer 'faked mugging to cover up petrol station brawl'|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/olympics/news/ryan-lochte-robbed-cctv-video-shows-us-swimmer-fighting-with-brazilian-security-guard-a7197601.html|publisher=The Independent|accessdate=2016-08-19|archive-date=2016-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818172844/http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/olympics/news/ryan-lochte-robbed-cctv-video-shows-us-swimmer-fighting-with-brazilian-security-guard-a7197601.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>美国奥委会随后向巴西方面致歉，<ref>{{cite web|title=Ryan Lochte 'robbery' case: USOC apologizes for swimmers' behavior|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/aug/19/ryan-lochte-rio-2016-robbery-story-usoc-statement|publisher=The Guardian|accessdate=2016-08-19|archive-date=2016-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160819090833/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/aug/19/ryan-lochte-rio-2016-robbery-story-usoc-statement|dead-url=no}}</ref>巴西警方则继续展开深入调查。四名运动员可能面临“破坏公物”和“报假警”的指控。<ref name="#2"/>本茨和康格于18日获准离境；<ref>{{cite web|title=U.S. swimmers Jack Conger, Gunnar Bentz allowed to go home Thursday night|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/olympics/rio-2016/2016/08/18/jack-conger-gunnar-bentz-fabricated-robbery-story-ryan-lochte/88980610/|publisher=USA Today|accessdate=2016-08-19|archive-date=2016-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160819042055/http://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/olympics/rio-2016/2016/08/18/jack-conger-gunnar-bentz-fabricated-robbery-story-ryan-lochte/88980610/|dead-url=no}}</ref>费根在同意向巴西慈善组织捐款11,000美元后被免于起诉，款项结清后即可离境。<ref>{{cite web|title=US Swimmer Jimmy Feigen Agrees to Pay $11K to Avoid Prosecution in Rio|url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/us-swimmer-jimmy-feigen-agrees-pay-11k-avoid/story?id=41507517|publisher=ABC News|accessdate=2016-08-19|archive-date=2016-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160819140828/http://abcnews.go.com/US/us-swimmer-jimmy-feigen-agrees-pay-11k-avoid/story?id=41507517|dead-url=no}}</ref>洛赫特也在19日发表声明，就此事向公众道歉。<ref>{{cite web|title=Ryan Lochte apologizes on social media|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/olympics/rio-2016/2016/08/19/ryan-lochte-apologizes-social-media/88991620/|publisher=USA Today|accessdate=2016-08-19|archive-date=2016-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160819214154/http://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/olympics/rio-2016/2016/08/19/ryan-lochte-apologizes-social-media/88991620/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

