ve-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160814035154/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/aug/09/olympic-swimming-yulia-efimova-fina-fallout|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/olympics/2016/08/07/rio-olympics-2016-tempers-flare-at-the-aquatics-centre-as-convic/|title=Rio Olympics 2016: Tempers flare at the Aquatics Centre as convicted drugs cheat Yulia Efimova returns to the pool|work=Telegraph|date=2016-08-08|accessdate=2016-08-14|archive-date=2016-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160811210916/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/olympics/2016/08/07/rio-olympics-2016-tempers-flare-at-the-aquatics-centre-as-convic/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/sport/olympics/36686211|title=Rio Olympics 2016: Russia's Yulia Efimova beaten to gold by Lilly King of USA|work=BBC|date=2016-08-09|accessdate=2016-08-14|archive-date=2016-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160812072512/http://www.bbc.com/sport/olympics/36686211|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/aug/09/yuilia-efimova-olympics-critics-cold-war-swimming-lilly-king-rio|title=Yulia Efimova hits back at critics: 'I thought cold war was long in the past'|work=The Guardian|date=2016-08-09|accessdate=2016-08-14|archive-date=2016-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160814033317/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/aug/09/yuilia-efimova-olympics-critics-cold-war-swimming-lilly-king-rio|dead-url=no}}</ref>

