=== 评论员言论爭議 ===
====涉嫌种族歧视====
8月11日，[[加拿大廣播公司|加拿大廣播公司]]（Canadian Broadcasting Corporation）評述員拜伦·麦克唐纳（Byron MacDonald，曾參與[[1972年夏季奧林匹克運動會|1972年夏季奧林匹克運動會]]）為賽事旁述期間，疑在忘記關麥克風的情況下，评论14歲中国女运动员[[艾衍含|艾衍含]]「died like a pig」（像豬一样死掉了），引发争议。随后加拿大广播公司立刻在[[Twitter|Twitter]]上多次致歉。大量观众认为此言论有种族歧视色彩，对此表达强烈的不满。之后麦克唐纳在直播中再次道歉，同时称此言论并非针对运动员个人，只是对她失误表现做出的评价，对运动员本身并无不尊重之意。<ref>{{cite news |title=加拿大播報員稱中國選手「死得像豬」 中國網民氣炸 |url=http://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/1792676 |accessdate= |agency= |date= |archive-date=2016-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815104648/http://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/1792676 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/aug/11/cbc-apology-died-like-a-pig-comment-chinese-swimmer-rio|title=CBC apologises for 'died like a pig' comment directed at Chinese swimmer|work=The Guardian|date=2016-08-11|accessdate=2016-08-14|archive-date=2016-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160814012510/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/aug/11/cbc-apology-died-like-a-pig-comment-chinese-swimmer-rio|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3735104/Viewers-CBC-s-Olympic-coverage-outraged-announcer-caught-mic-saying-Chinese-swimmer-went-like-stink-died-like-pig.html|title=Viewers of CBC's Olympic coverage outraged after 'racist' announcer is caught on mic saying 14-year-old Chinese swimmer 'went out like stink, died like a pig'|work=Daily Mail|date=2016-08-11|accessdate=2016-08-14|archive-date=2016-08-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160813103603/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3735104/Viewers-CBC-s-Olympic-coverage-outraged-announcer-caught-mic-saying-Chinese-swimmer-went-like-stink-died-like-pig.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

同日，前法國體操名將，[[2008年夏季奥林匹克运动会|北京奧運]][[跳馬|跳馬]]銀牌得主布埃爾（Thomas Bouhail）在[[推特|推特]]上称日本體操男團像是一群「小[[皮卡丘|皮卡丘]]」，又對日本女子隊伍也說出類似的話，這番言論引起争议。大量法国网民、法国視聽覺最高評議會和法国反种族歧视的组织认为类似言论涉嫌对日本人的[[種族歧視|種族歧視]]，布埃爾在Twitter上致歉。但也有部分日本网民称未感到被歧视，认为“这个比喻很可爱”。<ref>{{cite news|title=日本金牌體操選手是「小小皮卡丘」？　法國評論員挨轟歧視|url=http://sports.ettoday.net/news/753083#ixzz4HCX61UkD|accessdate=|agency=|date=|archive-date=2017-08-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170813185414/http://sports.ettoday.net/news/753083#ixzz4HCX61UkD|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nextshark.com/olympic-commentator-called-racist-calling-japanese-gymnasts-little-pikachus/|title=CULTURE Olympic Commentator Called Racist For Referring to Japanese Gymnasts as 'Little Pikachus'|work=Next Shark|date=2016-08-11|accessdate=2016-08-14|archive-date=2017-08-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170813223226/https://nextshark.com/olympic-commentator-called-racist-calling-japanese-gymnasts-little-pikachus/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

